A ranchette is another kind of suburban sprawl, usually on the outskirts of a major metropolitan area, and just past the planned neighborhoods.  The ranchette usually consists of 40 acres and a house and possibly a barn or other outbuildings.  Ranchettes are then usually further sub-developed as the growth of a city encompasses them.  Most ranchettes are not zoned and can become quite junky in a short time.  In the eastern deserts of Colorado the typical ranchette has the typical 40 acres and a moobile home.